ined as the total damage done divided by the amount of time spent at the camp. Melee classes therefore do a lower TDPS figure when there is more downtime.<br>- wizard's use their best DD spell for their level (no rains or AE). At level 60, wizards alternate casting Solist's Ice Spear and Draught of Ice.<br>- Wizard is not casting snare. Captured data indicates that snare automatically reduces damage output of the wizard when it is in use because of mana cost and increased agro.<br>- spells are 90% effective. The 10% damage loss comes from resists, fizzles, and concussion casts.<br>- Wizards are using their best familiar for the level.<br>- Wizards acquire their epic at level 55.<br>- Wizards are using the best chanter buff available at the level, but never glades or bard song.<br>- No figures account for any AA levels.<br>- Wizard Item graph assumes a wizard is using a Solist's Icy Wand starting at level 12, an Icicle Robe at level 50 (notice the drop in damage output), a Robe of Torrefaction (from Velketor) at level 55, and a Robe of Invocation (Rend Robe) at 60.<br>- Average combat length is 45 seconds.<br>- Melee damage data assumes relatively high end (twink) gear. FBSS at level 12, RBG at level 36, CoF at level 51, and ToVN haste item at 60.<br>- Melee damage assumes best chanter haste for the level is in use.<br>- There are many holes in the melee chart for raw data. I used measured data for my warrior twink at 18 and 20, measured data from Karnors in the 50-52 range, and measured data for melee classes at 60. Other data points are interpolated.<br><br>I will publish the spreadsheet in web form and downloadable form in the near future, once I add a page for easier manipulation of the figures. The spreadsheet itself has over 5000 numbers, but you only need about a dozen or so to tweak the interesting figures. The downloadable spreadsheet allows the user to play game designer and increase wizard damage, lower resists, reduce mana cost, etc. to try to produce a graph that is &quot;balanced.&quot; It's tougher than it looks <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :b --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/tongue.gif ALT=":b"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->     <br><br>Here are my links to the spreadsheets.<br><br>web version: <!--EZCODE AUTOLINK START--><a href="http://home.attbi.com/~dmoen/wizdps.htm">home.attbi.com/~dmoen/wizdps.htm</a><!--EZCODE AUTOLINK END--><br>excel version (zipped): <!--EZCODE AUTOLINK START--><a href="http://home.attbi.com/~dmoen/wizdps.zip">home.attbi.com/~dmoen/wizdps.zip</a><!--EZCODE AUTOLINK END--><br><br>Note: for both versions of the spreadsheets, you can access the different pages by clicking the tabs at the bottom of the screen. The first tab (controls) contains most of the tweakable data. For the web version, this shows you the values I used. For the Excel version, you can turn familiars on and off, add or remove a chanter or bard, turn on spellcasting fury and/or mental clarity, add FT items, etc. You can even edit the stats for right click nukes and change the level at which it is acquired. Also notice the impact that changing the engagment time has on right click nuke effectiveness.<br><br>Edit: put up spreadsheet links.<br><br>Edit2: version 1.1 of the spreadsheet accounts for melee proc damage.<br> <p>"Evacuate? In our moment of triumph? I think you overestimate their chances!"<BR>Armok Komra (Triton)<BR>Sorcerer of Povar</p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/uarmok.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Armok</A> at: 1/2/02 9:30:51 pm<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#33333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/usarta.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Sarta</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Wizard</span><br> <font color=#ffffff>(1/3/02 2:45:22 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub23.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm10.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=641.topic&index=1>Reply